column10: Sjá mynd og texta í tengdri frétt. "Þá hafa ýmis tímabundin verkefni hafa verið sett upp á svæðinu fyrir alla fjölskylduna. Á svæðinu er til að mynda hjólabrettavöllur, hjólaleikvöllur, körfuboltavöllur og matartorg með matarvögnum."

Hotel Borg has long been known for its luxurious and signature art deco style that characterizes the hotel throughout and appears in the smallest of details. Decorated with custom-made furniture and fittings, each room has its own individual charm.

Skúli Thoroddsen (1859-1916), Member of Althingi and editor, built at Vonarstræti 12 in 1908. Skúli lived there with his wife Theódóra Thoroddsen (1863-1954) poetess and their children until he died in 1916 but Theódóra lived in the house until 1930

In the grand stairway that leads through the center of the Apotek Hotel, the modern bright lift lights up the spiral staircase walk past original art from Iceland‘s well known sculptor Guðmundur Einarsson from Miðdalur (1895 – 1963).
